instructions:
*SCENARIO: Ordering from a coffee bar*
Imagine you're ordering a drink from the following menu:
*COFFEE BAR MENU - Assume all drinks are caffeinated for now; decaf NOT an option*
{{LIST *Matcha Latte* (12oz) (matcha concentrate + milk + foam),*Chai Latte* (12oz) (chai concentrate + milk + extra foam),*Latte* (12oz) (espresso + milk + foam),*Cappuccino* (8oz) (espresso + milk + extra foam),*Cortado* (4oz) (espresso + milk + extra foam),*Macchiato* (3oz) (espresso with a little foam),*Mocha* (12oz) (espresso + milk + chocolate + foam)}}
*CHOOSE YOUR DRINK*
{{ENTER drink drink Enter a drink from the list above.}}
{{ENTER menu_item_id drink Now write what you have entered above BUT (a) all in lowercase and (b) separated by hyphens ("-") and (c)  followed by any 4-digit number. For example, "Latte" would become "latte-0371". NO SPACES, NO QUOTES.}}

*MILK CHOICES - Assume 'whole milk' is the default option but you want a different milk*
{{LIST 2%, Non-Fat,Oat, 2% Lactose Free,Almond}}
{{ENTER milk1 milk Choose a type of milk from the list above}}
{{ENTER milk2 milk Choose a SECOND type of milk from the list above}}

*NAME* 
{{ENTER name name Enter a playing card name like "ace of spades" or "two of clubs"--CHOOSE YOUR OWN.}}

*TASK: Write the transcript of a conversation that you would have with the worker.* 
{{LIST Make this conversation sound like something you would expect at a real coffee bar,Make sure to use the words you would normally use to order these things---they don't have to match the menu exactly as long as they are common ways to order,The conversation will be written using the green and white dialog bubbles below (green dialog bubbles are for customer's turns and the white bubbles are for the worker's turns)}}
{{RAND order_id id 10000 99999}}
{{RAND order_item_id1 id 10000 99999}}
{{RAND order_item_id2 id 10000 99999}}

{{CONVERSATION
hint user (Suppose you were ordering *TWO* of these: var_drink. HOWEVER, for ONE of them you want var_milk1 milk while for the OTHER you want var_milk2 milk. How would YOU say this order?  *Say it out loud first*.)
call get_menu_items request {"query": "var_drink"}
response get_menu_items response {"menu_items":[{"menu_item_id":"var_menu_item_id","name":"var_drink"}]}
call get_addons request {"query": "var_milk1 milk OR var_milk2 milk", "menu_item_id":"var_menu_item_id"}
response get_addons response {"attributes": [{"attribute_id": "milk-options", "attribute_name": "Milk", "options":["No Milk", "Whole Milk","2% Milk", "Non-fat Milk", "Oat Milk","2% Lactose Free Milk", "Almond Milk"]}]}
call add_order_item request {"menu_item_id": "var_menu_item_id","quantity": "1","attributes": [{"attribute_id": "milk-options", "option":"var_milk1 Milk"}]}
response add_order_item response {"order_id": "var_order_id","order_item_id":"var_order_item_id1"}
call add_order_item request {"order_id": "var_order_id","menu_item_id": "var_menu_item_id","quantity": "1","attributes": [{"attribute_id": "milk-options", "option":"var_milk2 Milk"}]}
response add_order_item response {"order_id": "var_order_id","order_item_id":"var_order_item_id2"}
call get_order_details request {"order_id": "var_order_id"}
response get_order_details response {"order_id": "var_order_id", "attributes": [{"attribute_id": "name", "attribute_name": "Name", "option": "var_name"},{"attribute_id": "order-type", "attribute_name": "Order Type", "option": "here"}], "menu_items": [{"order_item_id": "var_order_item_id1", "menu_item_id": "var_menu_item_id", "menu_item_name": "var_drink", "quantity": "1", "attributes": [{"attribute_id": "milk-options", "option":"var_milk1 Milk"}]},{"order_item_id": "var_order_item_id2", "menu_item_id": "var_menu_item_id", "menu_item_name": "var_drink", "quantity": "1", "attributes": [{"attribute_id": "milk-options", "option":"var_milk2 Milk"}]}]}
hint assistant (Pretend the order is displayed to the customer but do NOT repeat the item name. The worker asks the customer to confirm the order is correct before sending it to the Coffee bar to be made --USE YOUR OWN WORDS).
hint user (answers yes)
call finish_order request {"order_id": "var_order_id"}
response finish_order response {"success":true}
hint assistant (Says OK and indicates the order will be ready shortly at the coffee bar-- USE YOUR OWN WORDS)
}}

{{CHECK confirm_flow  The conversation sounds realistic and logical.}}
{{CHECK confirm_language  The conversation contains no inappropriate language.}}

*SCENARIO: Ordering from a coffee bar*
Imagine you're ordering a drink from the following menu:

*COFFEE BAR MENU*
{{LIST *Cappuccino* (8oz) (espresso + milk + extra foam),*Cortado* (4oz) (espresso + milk + extra foam),*Macchiato* (3oz) (espresso with a little foam),*Mocha* (12oz) (espresso + milk + chocolate + foam)}}
*CHOOSE YOUR DRINK*
{{ENTER drink drink Enter a drink from the list above.}}
{{ENTER menu_item_id drink Now write what you have entered above BUT (a) all in lowercase and (b) separated by hyphens ("-") and (c)  followed by any 4-digit number. For example, "Latte" would become "latte-0371". NO SPACES. NO QUOTES}}

*NAME* 
{{ENTER name name Enter a playing card name like "ace of spades" or "two of clubs"--CHOOSE YOUR OWN.}}
*ESPRESSO SHOTS*
{{LIST Single, Double, Triple, Quadruple}}
{{ENTER shots shots Enter one of the above}}

*MILK CHOICES*
{{LIST Whole,2%, Non-Fat,Oat, 2% Lactose Free,Almond}}
{{ENTER milk milk Choose a type of milk from the list above}}

*Here or To go*
{{ENTER delivery delivery Enter either Here OR To go}}

*TASK: Write the transcript of a conversation that you would have with the worker.* 
{{LIST Make this conversation sound like something you would expect at a real coffee bar,Make sure to use the words you would normally use to order these things---they don't have to match the menu exactly as long as they are common ways to order,The conversation will be written using the green and white dialog bubbles below (green dialog bubbles are for customer's turns and the white bubbles are for the worker's turns)}}
{{RAND order_id id 10000 99999}}
{{RAND order_item_id id 10000 99999}}

{{CONVERSATION
hint user (1. Orders a var_shots var_drink with var_milk milk. 2. Specifies it is a "var_delivery" order. Say the order out loud, then write it here. MAKE SURE to add it is a 'var_delivery' order!)
call get_menu_items request {"query": "var_drink"}
response get_menu_items response {"menu_items":[{"menu_item_id":"var_menu_item_id","name":"var_drink"}]}
call get_addons request {"query": "var_shots OR var_milk Milk", "menu_item_id":"var_menu_item_id"}
response get_addons response {"attributes": [{"attribute_name": "Espresso Shots", "attribute_id": "espresso-shots", "options": ["Single","Double","Triple","Quadruple"]}, {"attribute_id": "milk-options", "attribute_name": "Milk", "options":["Whole Milk","2% Milk", "Non-fat Milk", "Oat Milk","2% Lactose Free Milk", "Almond Milk"]}]}

call add_order_item request {"menu_item_id": "var_menu_item_id","quantity": "1","attributes": [{"attribute_id": "espresso-shots", "option":"var_shots"},{"attribute_id": "milk-options", "option":"var_milk Milk"}]}
response add_order_item response {"order_id": "var_order_id","order_item_id":"var_order_item_id"}

call get_addons request {"query": "var_delivery", "scope": "order"}
response get_addons response {"attributes":[{"attribute_id": "order-type", "attribute_name": "Order Type", "options": ["Here", "To go", "Delivery"]}]}

call update_order request {"order_id": "var_order_id", "attributes": [{"attribute_id": "order-type", "option": "var_delivery"}] }
response update_order response {"order_id": "var_order_id"}

call get_order_details request {"order_id": "var_order_id"}
response get_order_details response {"order_id": "var_order_id", "attributes": [{"attribute_id": "name", "attribute_name": "Name", "option": "var_name"},{"attribute_id": "order-type", "attribute_name": "Order Type", "option": "var_delivery"}], "menu_items": [{"order_item_id": "var_order_item_id", "menu_item_id": "var_menu_item_id", "menu_item_name": "var_drink", "attributes": [{"attribute_id": "espresso-shots", "option":"var_shots"},{"attribute_id": "milk-options", "option":"var_milk Milk"}]}]}
force assistant OK. Just confirm the order all looks correct and I'll send it off to be made for you.
hint user (confirms it is correct)
call finish_order request {"order_id": "var_order_id"}
response finish_order response {"success":true}
hint assistant (Says OK and indicates the order will be ready shortly at the coffee bar-- USE YOUR OWN WORDS)
}}

